# Auto-deploy after changes

After making any code changes (edits, new files, fixes), run these commands to commit and push:

```powershell
git add .
git commit -m "Brief description of the change"
git push origin main
```

Use a clear, concise commit message describing what was changed. Do this as the final step after edits, unless the user asks not to.
